{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Vzhz1vsQcegmb1rAmFzVgE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0133GA9RitPc6xXN2Vcvgxot","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/25-2331e30/improvement-plan.md","old_string":"### Secondary fix: Improve preamble detection for garbled-then-clean sequences\n\nThe `findBurstEnd` function currently stops at the first non-garbled line. But when\nlines 1–3 are garbled fragments and line 4 is a short ALL_CAPS string, line 4 is very\nlikely part of the same overflow block.\n\n**Proposed heuristic:** After `findBurstEnd` skips garbled lines, if the next line is\nALL_CAPS and ≤ 3 words, AND the line after that starts with lowercase (body text), treat\nthe ALL_CAPS line as the tail of the preamble and skip it too.\n\n```typescript\n// In findBurstEnd, after the garbled-skip loop:\nif (i > 0 && i < lines.length) {\n  const next = lines[i].text;\n  // If burst ended at a short ALL_CAPS fragment followed by body text,\n  // it's likely the truncated title of the previous page's recipe.\n  if (isAllCaps(next) && wordCount(next) <= 3 && i + 1 < lines.length) {\n    const afterNext = lines[i + 1].text;\n    if (/^[a-ząćęłńóśźż]/.test(afterNext) && wordCount(afterNext) >= 4) {\n      i++;  // Skip the ALL_CAPS fragment too\n      // Also skip the body text that follows (same prose-preamble logic)\n      // ...\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis is a **complementary** fix. It prevents `DAT FLATBREADS` from entering the candidate\npool at all, which is cleaner than relying solely on corroboration to remove it later.\nHowever, corroboration is the more general defense (handles cases where the preamble\ndetection doesn't fire).\n\n**Risk:** Could skip a legitimate short ALL_CAPS title at the start of a file if preceded\nby garbled text. Mitigation: Only fires when `i > 0` (garbled lines were actually\nskipped) AND the next line is body text (lowercase start, ≥ 4 words). A real title would\ntypically be followed by a subtitle or description, not body text.\n\n### Implementation changes","new_string":"### Implementation changes"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1179,"cache_read_input_tokens":35591,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1179},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a061f1f0-ad7a-459c-9eae-0adb758ccdd2","uuid":"7a7c4954-8d3f-4e9e-a225-c07b75fcce11"}
