{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016Qw3qz7mx7niFzUdY5HA5g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Y1Ah51GKVikZb4kaWLpKLX","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/25-2331e30/improvement-plan.md","old_string":"3. **Should `findBurstEnd` improvement be included?** It's a belt-and-suspenders approach.\n   The corroboration check alone would fix the failure. The preamble detection improvement\n   prevents the artifact from entering the candidate pool at all, which is cleaner.\n   **Recommendation:** Include both. They address different layers of the pipeline and\n   neither is risky on its own.\n\n---","new_string":"3. ~~**Should `findBurstEnd` improvement be included?**~~ Removed — analysis showed that\n   `findBurstEnd` doesn't skip the garbled preamble lines (they're long, not short), so\n   the proposed `i > 0` guard would never fire. A preamble detection improvement may be\n   worth pursuing in a future iteration if new failures surface, but it requires a\n   different approach (handling long garbled lines, not just short ones).\n\n---"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":321,"cache_read_input_tokens":37995,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":321},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a061f1f0-ad7a-459c-9eae-0adb758ccdd2","uuid":"6058cd8b-7493-4f57-859a-b55eaaf442e4"}
