{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0114d2nCxsydEVhkxXaCpYnW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Validation Complete\n\n**Status: Ready** (after fixes applied)\n\n### What was fixed in the plan:\n\n1. **Removed the secondary `findBurstEnd` fix** — it was based on the false premise that lines 1–3 are short (<20 chars) and get skipped by the garbled-line loop. In reality they're 70–200+ chars, so `findBurstEnd` returns 0 and the `i > 0` guard would never fire. Dead code for this case.\n\n2. **Corrected the root cause analysis** — now accurately describes why `findBurstEnd` doesn't detect the preamble (long lines, digit-prefixed lines) instead of incorrectly claiming it skips lines 1–3.\n\n3. **Simplified implementation phases** from 4 steps to 3 (removed the `findBurstEnd` step).\n\n4. **Updated Open Question #3** — marked as resolved with explanation of why the secondary fix doesn't work.\n\n### What's good about the plan:\n\n- **Primary fix (corroboration score)** is well-designed, clearly specified, and sufficient on its own\n- All 3 feedback mitigation directions are considered; 2 of 3 are directly addressed by the corroboration score\n- Performance analysis is sound (negligible vs embedding computation)\n- Testing strategy is focused and appropriate\n- No overengineering — the tiered threshold is justified, not premature"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":305,"cache_read_input_tokens":38716,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":305},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a061f1f0-ad7a-459c-9eae-0adb758ccdd2","uuid":"7c477555-4a20-4e43-b822-cd42b7b77c19"}
